\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Independence
\series default
: 
\begin_inset Formula \(Cov( Z_{mi}, \epsilon_i) = 0\)
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula \(m\)
\end_inset

. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Relevance
\series default
: In the second stage regression, the variables 
\begin_inset Formula \[
      \left( \widehat{X}_{1i},\dots,\widehat{X}_{ki}, W_{1i},\dots,W_{ri}, 1 \right)
      \]
\end_inset

are not perfectly multicollinear. 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
What does the relevance condition mean? 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset Separator plain

\end_inset


\end_layout

