\begin_layout Itemize
Instruments are 
\series bold
weak
\series default
 if those instruments explain little variation in the endogenous variables. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Weak instruments lead to
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
tightlist
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
imprecise estimates (higher standard errors) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The asymptotic distribution would deviate from a normal distribution even if we have a large sample. 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Here is a rule of thumb to check the relevance conditions. 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset Separator plain

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame

\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
tightlist
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Consider the case with one endogenous variable 
\begin_inset Formula \(X_{1i}\)
\end_inset

. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The first stage regression
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula \[
  X_k = \pi_0 + \pi_1 Z_{1i} + \cdots + \pi_M Z_{Mi} + \pi_{M+1} W_{1i} + \cdots + \pi_{M+R} W_{Ri}
  \]
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
And test the null hypothesis 
\begin_inset Formula \[
  \begin{aligned}
  H_0 & : \pi_1 = \cdots = \pi_M = 0 \\ 
  H_1 & : otherwise
  \end{aligned}
  \]
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
tightlist
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This is F test (test of joint hypothesis) 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If we can reject this, we can say no concern for weak instruments. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A rule of thumbs is that the F statistic should be larger than 10. 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
